{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"86141a663c2eb7543d1a51ec6253a1d54de912fd"},"timestamp":1338872214,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0OTAyMjc3","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/782","origin":"github"},"title":" /usr/local/lib/parrot/4.4.0-devel/parrot_config.o: Permission denied","message":"`make install` fails if you don't have write permissions to /usr/local.\n\n`sudo make install` creates `src/install_config.o` as root with perm 600.\nThen copies `src/install_config.o` to [lib] `parrot_config.o` with perms _600_ as user _root_, \nwhich subsequently fails when building rakudo, or any other hll.\n\nEnsure proper read permissions in tools/dev/install_files.pl, 644.\nOr ensure 644 after compiling.\n\nA workaround is to do `make installable` before `sudo make install`.","files":null}]}